body:
Hi @superical, I couldn't reproduce this. Here's the contract I used:

```solidity
contract Foo {
  function f() public {
    require(false, "boom");
  }
}
```

and here's the test:

```js
it("test", async function () {
  const [s] = await ethers.getSigners();
  const foo = await ethers.deployContract("Foo");


  // normal call
  const tx1 = foo.f();
  await expect(tx1).to.be.revertedWith("boom");

  // sent from signer
  const tx2 = s.sendTransaction({
    to: foo.address,
    data: "0x26121ff0", // selector of f()
  });

  await expect(tx2).to.be.revertedWith("boom");
});
```

And it worked fine.

I'm going to tentatively close this, but I'm happy to re-open it if you can provide a [minimal reproducible example](https://stackoverflow.com/help/minimal-reproducible-example)
